apm.name: Holistic Client App Runtime Kernel
apm.description: This model manages, tracks, and controls the lifecycle of the client application.

process.name: [PPL45jw5RDWSMNsB97WIWg::Holistic Client App Runtime Kernel] APM Digraph
process.description: This model manages, tracks, and controls the lifecycle of the client application.

p.description: Hooking DOM events pertinent to tracking the lifecycle of this instance of the client application running inside the user's browser.
Start core client app kernel subsystems.
Query the derived client app for information required to initialize the core client app runtime.
Wait for the core client app kernel subsystems to become available.
Wait for the browser to finish loading the HTML document and its referenced external resources (scripts, CSS, images, fonts, JSON, ...
Access the boot ROM embedded in the hosting HTML document to get the suspended process state of the derived application.
Load the deserialized app into the OCD to initialize the client app runtime.
Initialize the view and d2r2/React display models. Performs a d2r2/ReactDOM.hydrate operation ultimately.
The client application is online and awaiting input from external actors.
Client application process boot failed due to unrecoverable error(s).
Client application process resume failured due to unrecoverable error(s).
Client application process crashed at runtime due to unexpected and unrecoverable error(s).
